==Dutch==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|odt|nl}} {{recons|hervist|lang=odt}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|nl}} {{recons|harbistaz|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|nl}} {{recons|kerp-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|skerp-|lang=ine-pro}}. Related to High German {{term|Herbst|lang=de}}, Low German {{term|harvst|lang=nds}}, West Frisian {{term|hjerst|lang=fy}}, English {{term|harvest|lang=en}}, also Latin {{term|carpere||to [[pick]], to [[pluck]]|lang=la}}, Greek {{term|καρπός|tr=karpos||fruit, harvest|lang=grc}}. The original meaning is ''harvest time'', as is seen in {{term|herfstmaand|lang=nl}}.

from {{etyl|gem-pro|de}} {{recons|harbistaz|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|de}} {{recons|kerp-|lang=ine-pro}}, {{recons|skerp-|lang=ine-pro}}. Compare Dutch {{term|herfst|lang=nl}}, Low German {{term|harvst|lang=nds}}, West Frisian {{term|hjerst|lang=fy}}, English {{term|harvest|lang=en}}.
