====Usage notes====
The made-up compound noun {{term||herfstschrik|fear of Autumn}} ({{IPA|/hɛrfstsxrɪk/|lang=nl}}, {{X-SAMPA|/hErfstsxrIk/}}) is used to demonstrate the bewildering number of consonants that can be strung together in Dutch. It is not particularly difficult for a speaker of Dutch to pronounce all consonants, but in practice a few of these will be dropped to something like {{IPA|/hɛrfsxrɪk/|lang=nl}}, {{X-SAMPA|/hErfsxrIk/}}.

